  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This package evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The intended use scope — predicting normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) within ±15% for operating points 2500–5000 RPM and 2–8 L/min flow — is described in the bound requirement and claim nodes. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed; seven factors show achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels, and six factors were assessed with gaps noted. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across inlet viscosity, hematocrit, and pump geometry tolerances. Decision: Accepted with conditions recorded in the decision record.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-class3",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-vad-nih-prediction",
